# .chktexrc — local chktex configuration for "Jiterati: A Vademecum"
#
# Why this file exists
# --------------------
# chktex looks for a global resource file and prints
#   "chktex: WARNING -- Could not find global resource file."
# when none is found. The presence of a *local* .chktexrc in the working
# directory (even a comment-only one) satisfies that lookup, so
#   chktex Jiterati-Vademcum.tex
# runs cleanly. This file additionally tunes chktex for the genre.
#
# Syntax note
# -----------
# chktexrc directives use `Key Value` (or `Key=Value`). Command-line
# style flags are passed via the `CmdLine { ... }` directive, which is
# appended to the real command line. Warning numbers are muted with
# `-n <num>`. See `chktex -h` for the full option list.

# --- Genre tuning -----------------------------------------------------------
# This is a technical textbook: heavy on verbatim code, mathematics,
# identifiers set in monospace, command names ending with punctuation,
# and inline snippets. A handful of chktex warnings are steady false
# positives in that setting, so we mute them here rather than littering
# the prose with per-line suppressions:
#
#   1  command terminated with space      (macro names followed by code)
#   8  wrong length of dash               (deliberate -- ranges in prose)
#   11 ellipsis style suggestions
#   13 inter-sentence spacing             (code identifiers near periods)
#   22 typographic quote suggestions      (we use straight quotes in code)
#   26 solo punctuation in math/code
#   36 use of `...'                       (literal ellipses in output)
#   38 quote/dash stylistic suggestions
CmdLine { -n 1 -n 8 -n 11 -n 13 -n 22 -n 26 -n 36 -n 38 }

# Genuine mistakes (unbalanced braces/delimiters, bad \label usage,
# missing $...$ math, etc.) are left enabled.
